Initializes a new instance of the error message with a default message indicating that no chain was supplied to the client.

<Note>
  `FetchError` extends `BaseError`, see the docs for BaseError for all supported
  methods.
</Note>

## Import

```ts
import { FetchError } from "@alchemy/common";
```

## Parameters

### route

`string`

- The route that failed to fetch.

### method

`string`

- The HTTP method that was used.

### cause

`Error`

- The cause of the error.
